UPDATE courses SET
    course_description = '<p>A Bachelor of Arts degree enables you to study what you are passionate about in life, and to gather skills that will prepare for the work place and a wide variety of careers. You have the flexibility to choose from a broad range of majors and minors, taught face to face, online, and on different campuses. You will take 30 units of Core courses across the BA degree, enabling you to become part of a common group in your first year and to focus on specific knowledge and skills you need to obtain for success. You can tailor the remainder of your program to match your specific interests, including pursuing themes and disciplines, gaining work experience, engaging with industry, and completing research projects.</p><p>Some majors/minors are offered predominantly at one campus and others are offered at both the Callaghan and Ourimbah campus or online. The availability of courses within the below listed majors/minors are subject to change.</p><p>The offerings in the Bachelor of Arts are diverse. Students must complete at least one major, with options to complement this with a second major, pair of minors or a range of electives. The Program requirements are detailed below.</p><p><strong>Majors and Minors:</strong></p><p><strong>Minors only:</strong></p><p><em>All majors and minors are available at Callaghan campus, with the exception of Performing Arts and International Relations and Screen and Cultural Studies which are available at Newcastle City campus. </em> </p><p><em>The majors and minors available Online are: English and Writing, Screen and Cultural Studies, French Studies, Global Indigenous Studies, History, Japanese Studies, Psychology Studies, and Sociology and Anthropology.</em> </p><p><em>The availability of courses within majors and minors are subject to change.</em> </p>',
    onshore_tuition_fee = '',
    offshore_tuition_fee = '',
