UPDATE courses SET
    course_description = '<p>The combined Bachelor of Business/Bachelor of Media Communication program is an interdisciplinary degree designed to equip students with a wide range of skills and knowledge necessary to thrive in the dynamic and ever-changing professional landscape. This program combines the applied approach of the Bachelor of Business with the global industry perspective of the Bachelor of Media Communication, providing students with a unique blend of business acumen and communication expertise.</p><p>In the Bachelor of Business component, students gain a comprehensive and practical understanding of crucial business areas such as innovation, business analytics, marketing, management, and finance. The six distinctive majors available within the degree cater to diverse career aspirations, specifically: innovation and entrepreneurship, marketing, leadership and management, human resources management, international relations, and international business.</p><p>The Bachelor of Media and Communication component prepares students to create text, vision, and sound-based content for different purposes and for a variety of organisations, individuals, and institutions. Students learn to connect theory and practice, collaborate with local and global communities, and effect positive change by creating and designing industry-relevant solutions to important societal and global issues. The three media and communication majors available are: Media Production, News Media, and Public Relations.</p>',
