UPDATE courses SET
    course_description = '<p>The Bachelor of Commerce program is the first step to becoming a fully qualified accountant or in undertaking a career in finance or economics. The unique program structure at the Newcastle Business School offers industry-relevant and authentic applied curricula with two study options to complete the program. Students are able to choose either two majors or one major with two minors within the program. That is students can choose between accounting, economics, or finance. The Bachelor of Commerce program is designed to empower students with contemporary theoretical, technical, and practical business knowledge and essential skills to thrive in a business environment with rapid digital transformation and a focus on sustainability goals. The program embeds innovative and applied problem-solving, instills an entrepreneurial mindset and career-ready skills required in the dynamic workforce. With accounting and financial management at the very heart of all organisations, students will find commerce to be a field offering enormous scope and opportunity in embarking on a career journey in the global business world.</p><p>All majors are available for study at Newcastle City Precinct.</p><p>Major offered at Ourimbah is Accounting. </p><p>Majors offered at PSB Singapore are: Accounting and Finance.</p><p><em><strong>Greater Bank Finance Lab</strong> - Located on level one of the University’s new state of the art CBD vertical campus, NUspace, the <a href="https://www.newcastle.edu.au/school/newcastle-business-school/greater-bank-finance-lab" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" target="target">Greater Bank Finance Lab</a> is a hands-on learning environment, enabling University of Newcastle Business School students to build their skills in financial decision making, risk management and economic systems, before they graduate.</em> </p>',
