UPDATE courses SET
    course_description = '<p>The Master of Data Science and Artificial Intelligence (AI) program at the University of Newcastle marries the rigorous analysis of data science with the transformative potential of modern AI technologies. This program not only covers the core principles of data management and analysis but also dives deep into critical aspects of AI, including ethics, deep learning, and generative AI. Given the rapid advancement in the scientific and technological sectors, there is an unprecedented surge in data creation, elevating the demand for professionals skilled in navigating this complex landscape.</p><p>This program is designed to prepare graduates to thrive in various sectors by equipping them with skills in data handling, analysis, interpretation, and visualisation. It emphasises real-world application, ensuring students can translate theoretical knowledge into practical solutions across diverse industries. Students will become proficient in using sophisticated data to model real-world scenarios and communicate insights effectively.</p><p>The curriculum is professionally oriented and grounded in industry practices, focusing on applied problem-solving and advanced computing techniques. Core courses offer an introduction to Python programming, a comprehensive refresher in mathematics, and essential topics such as data wrangling, visualisation, statistics, databases, predictive analytics, big data techniques, and an introduction to machine intelligence.</p><p>Students have the opportunity to specialise in either Computational Intelligence or Health Data Analysis. The Computational Intelligence specialisation adopts a computer science approach, enhancing knowledge in big data, predictive analytics, applied AI, advanced databases, cybersecurity fundamentals, and associated ethical considerations. Alternatively, the Health Data Analysis track provides a deep dive into medical statistics and biostatistics, supplying transferable skills relevant to other domains as well.</p><p>This accessible AI-centric educational experience ensures graduates are not just participants but leaders in the ongoing data and AI revolution, ready to tackle challenges and innovate in a data-driven world.</p>',
    onshore_tuition_fee = '',
    offshore_tuition_fee = '',
    entry_requirements = '<div class="css-1bxk47o-Box--Box-Box-Card--CardBody e12hqxty1"><div class="css-yd08g9-Box--Box-Box-Attribute--AttrContainer ene3w3n3" display=""><div class="css-t643gp-Attribute--AttrBody ene3w3n1" data-testid="AttrBody"><div class="css-19qn38w-Box--Box-Box-Flex--Flex-Flex e8qda2r1"> </div><div class="css-1nx81rv-Attribute--AttributeChildrenWrap ene3w3n0"><div class="css-apyj4p-Box--Box-Box-Card--CardBody e12hqxty1"><ul> <li>Students with a three-year, Bachelor degree (AQF level 7) or higher in a different discipline area (also called non-cognate discipline) to data science and their chosen specialisation are eligible to undertake the 160 unit program. </li> <li>Students with a three-year Bachelor degree (AQF level 7) or higher in a non-cognate discipline who also hold a minimum of five years demonstrable Recognised Prior Learning (RPL) in an area related to data science and/or their chosen specialisation (also called cognate discipline) may be eligible to study between 120 and 160 units, inclusive.</li> <li>Students with a three-year Bachelor degree (AQF level 7) or Bachelor (Honours) (AQF 8) in a cognate discipline to data science and/or their specialisation may be eligible to study between 120 and 160 units, inclusive.</li> <li>Students with a Graduate Certificate or Graduate Diploma (AQF level 8) in a cognate discipline to data science and/or data analytics may be eligible to study 120 units, inclusive.</li> </ul> </div></div></div></div></div><div aria-label="English language requirements accordions" class="css-1d7k8gv-Box--Box-Box-Card--Card-Card-EmptyCard--EmptyCard-styled--SAccordionContainer e1s7etki7" elevation="2" id="Englishlanguagerequirements-7f747c44-ad7c-457d-9361-8336fff7c5c6" name="ACCORDION_CONTAINER" role="list"><div class="false css-rg4i61-Box--Box-Box-Flex--Flex-Flex-styled--SAccordionHeader e1s7etki6"><p style="font-weight: bold;" class="css-1b0v7mv-Accordions--HeadingWithSizing-ComponentHeading--ComponentHeading e191